<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,1510,1717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,1510,1536]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,1517,1534]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,1510,1536]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">.</emphasis>
The bright green basal area of the fore wings and bright red on the basal area of the hind wings easily distinguish species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[513,642,1547,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Hemisciera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[513,642,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Hemisciera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[810,923,1546,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Fidicinini">Fidicinini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,1510,1717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,219,1582,1608]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,350,1589,1606]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">DISTRIBUTION</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[350,357,1582,1608]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">.</emphasis>
The genus has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[756,827,1582,1608]" name="Brazil" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[840,935,1582,1608]" name="Ecuador" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1117,1582,1608]" name="French Guiana" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1221,1583,1609]" name="Panama" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Panama</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1281,1332,1583,1609]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[235,407,1618,1644]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="377 - 418" refId="ref107675" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2011 a) Checklist of the cicadas of French Guiana including new records and the description of nine new species (Insecta, Hemiptera, Cicadoidea, Cicadidae). Zoosystema, 33, 377 - 418. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2011 n 3 a 6" type="journal article" year="2011">Sanborn 2011a</bibRefCitation>
; 2013; 2018b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S." box="[574,839,1618,1644]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref108909" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Sanborn &amp; Heath 2014</bibRefCitation>
). References to 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1128,1618,1644]" name="Argentina" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1184,1266,1618,1644]" name="Bolivia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
are considered to be misinterpretations of an original source by 
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[689,869,1654,1681]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf (1963a)</bibRefCitation>
and were removed recently from the cicada faunae of these countries (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[363,541,1690,1717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
